In other words, if we know that the alien visited Mars, it logically follows that the robot also visited Jupiter.

2. "The robot might not have visited Jupiter." This statement suggests that there is a possibility that the robot did not visit Jupiter, even though the previous statement implies a necessity for the robot to visit Jupiter if the alien visited Mars.
